Our $1.00 stock portfolio also provides us an example of how we might fix these rebalancing distortions. We form wealth relatives for each of the succeeding months. We aggregate stocks and then use portfolio relatives as prices to determine corrected returns. Specifically, the stockiwealth relatives through month 12 are

               If there are no delistings of stocks in the size decile, the calculation of wealth relatives is straightforward. We sum across the individual stock wealth relatives each month for portfolio wealth. However, if a firm delists, the delisted wealth must be accounted for. To control for delisting effects, at the end of the month of delisting, we distribute the delisted wealth in equal proportion to the surviving firms in the portfolio. Let
                  \documentclass{aastex} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{bm} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{pifont} \usepackage{stmaryrd} \usepackage{textcomp} \usepackage{portland,xspace} \usepackage{amsmath,amsxtra} \usepackage[OT2,OT1]{fontenc} \newcommand\cyr{ \renewcommand\rmdefault{wncyr} \renewcommand\sfdefault{wncyss} \renewcommand\encodingdefault{OT2} \normalfont \selectfont} \DeclareTextFontCommand{\textcyr}{\cyr} \pagestyle{empty} \DeclareMathSizes{10}{9}{7}{6} \begin{document} \landscape $\gamma _{t}$ \end{document}
